PHASE-5 PROTECTION DIRECTIVE

1. Existing database columns MUST NOT be:
   - deleted
   - renamed
   - repurposed
   - type-changed

2. Existing tables MUST NOT be:
   - dropped
   - structurally modified (unless explicitly mentioned)

3. Existing services MUST NOT be altered:
   - MutationService
   - ConflictDetectionService
   - Lifecycle logic
   - ProfileCompletionService (except adding new section weight=0)

4. Any new feature must:
   - use NEW tables
   - use NEW snapshot keys
   - use additive migrations only
   - NOT remove or modify existing wizard sections

5. Old data must remain valid after new migrations.

6. If any change risks existing flow:
   STOP and report instead of auto-refactoring.
